419
00:22:50,082 --> 00:22:52,081
(Ground meat, egg, green onion, seasoned salt, )

420
00:22:52,082 --> 00:22:53,962
(soy sauce, cooking wine, Korean pancake flour)

421
00:22:54,552 --> 00:22:59,821
(Step 1: Whisk the eggs to make the base.)

422
00:22:59,822 --> 00:23:03,322
(You need to whisk hard to make them smooth.)

423
00:23:05,462 --> 00:23:09,332
(Is he seasoning the eggs?)

424
00:23:10,732 --> 00:23:14,802
(In general, the seasoning goes on the meat.)

425
00:23:15,602 --> 00:23:17,841
(Seasoned salt, soy sauce, pepper, cooking wine)

426
00:23:17,842 --> 00:23:21,541
(If you add the seasoning directly to the egg base, )

427
00:23:21,542 --> 00:23:23,811
(they will penetrate the meatball evenly...)

428
00:23:23,812 --> 00:23:26,082
(without clumping.)

429
00:23:27,312 --> 00:23:31,082
(It will create a texture that is flavorful and tender.)

430
00:23:31,122 --> 00:23:34,952
(Shaking it to mix the seasoning well)

431
00:23:37,862 --> 00:23:40,492
(Once the egg base is ready, )

432
00:23:41,462 --> 00:23:44,001
(massage in some green onions...)

433
00:23:44,002 --> 00:23:46,602
(and ground meat.)

434
00:23:46,902 --> 00:23:52,002
(You must make sure the meat absorbs the egg base.)

435
00:23:53,772 --> 00:23:56,412
(The batter for Korean meatballs is ready.)

436
00:23:56,812 --> 00:24:01,482
