01:21:14,604 --> 01:21:16,374
(when it had been going smoothly?)

1579
01:21:17,274 --> 01:21:19,984
(Si Jin comes out to check the situation again.)

1580
01:21:20,284 --> 01:21:21,783
I'm sorry. Was the salad served already?

1581
01:21:21,784 --> 01:21:24,683
Yes. We had the salad and the side dishes already.

1582
01:21:24,684 --> 01:21:27,454
(The customers say that they had the salad already.)

1583
01:21:27,684 --> 01:21:29,924
Table 13 is already served.

1584
01:21:30,054 --> 01:21:31,424
- So...
- Table 13?

1585
01:21:31,954 --> 01:21:33,593
- Yes.
- Then why did we get the order?

1586
01:21:33,594 --> 01:21:34,994
The other table needs to be served.

1587
01:21:35,224 --> 01:21:36,263
Table 13?

1588
01:21:36,264 --> 01:21:39,134
(The three of them put their heads together.)

1589
01:21:40,334 --> 01:21:41,663
What? Then why...

1590
01:21:41,664 --> 01:21:43,804
(They don't really get it even if they look at it.)

1591
01:21:44,304 --> 01:21:46,444
Are we behind with the meat for Table 13, then?

1592
01:21:47,574 --> 01:21:48,903
No, they ordered it again.

1593
01:21:48,904 --> 01:21:50,064
- Did they reorder it?
- Yes.

1594
01:21:50,374 --> 01:21:51,673
No, they ordered it again.

1595
01:21:51,674 --> 01:21:52,783
- Did they reorder it?
- Yes.

1596
01:21:52,784 --> 01:21:55,714
They had the side salad and ordered a main salad.

1597
01:21:56,014 --> 01:21:57,254
You can take your time.

1598
01:21:58,384 --> 01:22:00,824
(This was what happened.)

1599
01:22:01,854 --> 01:22:03,453
(The table only ordered the side dishes.)

1600
01:22:03,454 --> 01:22:05,354
(Beef tartare 1, japchae 1)

1601
01:22:05,894 --> 01:22:11,164
(The side dishes don't come with a salad.)

1602
01:22:12,094 --> 01:22:16,374
(But Chef Paik served it as complimentary.)

1603
01:22:16,874 --> 01:22:20,104
(So the complimentary salad was given to them.)

1604
01:22:20,374 --> 01:22:21,443
I like the sauce.

1605
01:22:21,444 --> 01:22:23,444
Yes, it's very good.

1606
01:22:24,614 --> 01:22:27,644
(So they enjoyed the complimentary salad.)

1607
01:22:28,314 --> 01:22:31,354
(And then, they ordered the main course too.)

1608
01:22:31,854 --> 01:22:33,283
- You don't have to rush it.
- Okay.

1609
01:22:33,284 --> 01:22:34,954
(The matter has been settled.)

1610
01:22:36,024 --> 01:22:37,053
- For two?
- Yes.

1611
01:22:37,054 --> 01:22:38,100
(He quickly prepares a pan of the squid and pork.)

1612
01:22:38,124 --> 01:22:41,394
- Table 13.
- Table 13. Please give me a second.

1613
01:22:42,694 --> 01:22:43,963
(The complimentary salad brought in additional 36 euros.)

1614
01:22:43,964 --> 01:22:45,094
- Here.
- Thank you.

1615
01:22:45,364 --> 01:22:46,804
May I take your glasses?

1616
01:22:47,664 --> 01:22:50,174
(It's been one hour since opening.)

1617
01:22:50,404 --> 01:22:51,873
- Hello.
- Hello.

1618
01:22:51,874 --> 01:22:54,574
(The real dinner time begins.)

1619
01:22:54,674 --> 01:22:56,513
- Would you like to sit here then?
- Yes. Perfect.

1620
01:22:56,514 --> 01:22:57,544
Thank you.

1621
01:22:57,614 --> 01:22:59,984
(More customers are coming to the Single Pan House.)

1622
01:23:02,644 --> 01:23:04,784
(Two people are passing by.)

1623
01:23:08,084 --> 01:23:09,183
(Turning)

1624
01:23:09,184 --> 01:23:11,394
(They turn back to come to the Single Pan House.)

1625
01:23:12,054 --> 01:23:14,663
- Hello. We're 2 people.
- Hello. You're 2?

1626
01:23:14,664 --> 01:23:17,864
We have seating outside over there or upstairs.

1627
01:23:17,964 --> 01:23:19,194
- Outside.
- Yes? Okay.

1628
01:23:20,864 --> 01:23:23,734
(The young couple takes the table outside, )

1629
01:23:25,034 --> 01:23:27,574
(and the outdoor seating is full.)

1630
01:23:27,974 --> 01:23:30,713
(Carefully reading the menu)

1631
01:23:30,714 --> 01:23:32,394
There's only one page. This is for drinks.

1632
01:23:33,684 --> 01:23:35,044
Yes, because it's...

1633
01:23:35,814 --> 01:23:37,714
Korean barbecue.

1634
01:23:38,554 --> 01:23:40,835
I don't know if you've seen it, but it has a big grill...

1635
01:23:42,184 --> 01:23:44,694
in the middle of the table, and you grill stuff.

1636
01:23:45,354 --> 01:23:48,124
(This right here!)

1637
01:23:52,134 --> 01:23:54,734
(Another couple is interested in the Single Pan House.)

1638
01:23:57,934 --> 01:23:59,734
- Do you have a table for 2?
- A table for 2?

1639
01:24:01,474 --> 01:24:02,944
Do we have a table for two upstairs?

1640
01:24:03,114 --> 01:24:04,674
- Yes, we do.
- We do, right?

1641
01:24:06,214 --> 01:24:07,584
- Upstairs, please.
- Yes.

1642
01:24:08,344 --> 01:24:10,513
- Hello.
- Welcome.

1643
01:24:10,514 --> 01:24:11,514
Welcome!

1644
01:24:12,214 --> 01:24:15,324
(The customers sit at the table for 4 on the 2nd floor.)

1645
01:24:16,254 --> 01:24:18,994
(Pulling)

1646
01:24:19,694 --> 01:24:21,664
(Roxana creates another seating.)

1647
01:24:22,194 --> 01:24:24,294
(She is determined to get another team.)

1648
01:24:25,394 --> 01:24:28,204
(Thanks to her, another couple comes in.)

1649
01:24:29,004 --> 01:24:31,804
(And the indoor seating is full too.)

1650
01:24:32,374 --> 01:24:33,773
(Adding 62 euros: 2 spicy stir-fried squid and pork, )

1651
01:24:33,774 --> 01:24:35,004
(1 tteokgalbi, 1 soju)

1652
01:24:35,244 --> 01:24:36,313
(Adding 75 euros: 2 spicy stir-fried squid and pork, )

1653
01:24:36,314 --> 01:24:38,434
(tteokgalbi, beef tartare, grapefruit and lemon soju)

1654
01:24:38,614 --> 01:24:39,743
(Adding 56 euros: 2 spicy stir-fried squid and pork, )

1655
01:24:39,744 --> 01:24:41,084
(lemon soju, grapefruit soju)

1656
01:24:41,784 --> 01:24:42,983
(Current sales: 995 euros)

1657
01:24:42,984 --> 01:24:46,624
(They achieved a full house.)

1658
01:24:47,284 --> 01:24:49,654
(Staring at the order sheets)

1659
01:24:50,424 --> 01:24:51,654
We need 5 orders for 2.

1660
01:24:51,694 --> 01:24:53,524
- Did you say 5 orders for 2?
- Yes.

1661
01:24:54,194 --> 01:24:56,694
(Work is piling up for Chef Paik.)

1662
01:24:57,594 --> 01:25:00,464
(The volume of the orders is great as there are many customers.)

1663
01:25:04,074 --> 01:25:05,504
(Smiling)

1664
01:25:05,674 --> 01:25:07,544
It looks so good.

1665
01:25:10,474 --> 01:25:12,884
(Torching it to look even more delicious)

1666
01:25:14,484 --> 01:25:17,184
(Adding the smoky flavor)

1667
01:25:17,654 --> 01:25:19,983
(Squid)

1668
01:25:19,984 --> 01:25:21,353
(Paik mushroom)

1669
01:25:21,354 --> 01:25:23,794
(Chilis)

1670
01:25:24,694 --> 01:25:25,724
Done.

1671
01:25:28,194 --> 01:25:29,533
- Table Seven.
- Okay.

1672
01:25:29,534 --> 01:25:31,094
(Pan of the squid and pork: 1 out of 5)

1673
01:25:31,534 --> 01:25:33,034
You can keep making the pan for two.

1674
01:25:33,334 --> 01:25:34,364
Okay.

1675
01:25:34,664 --> 01:25:37,144
(Feeling like a master of the spicy stir-fried squid and pork)

1676
01:25:37,774 --> 01:25:38,833
Done.

1677
01:25:38,834 --> 01:25:40,374
(Pan of the squid and pork: 2 out 5)

1678
01:25:41,374 --> 01:25:43,414
(He keeps producing the pan of the squid and pork.)

1679
01:25:45,074 --> 01:25:46,983
(Pan of the squid and pork: 3 out 5)

1680
01:25:46,984 --> 01:25:48,044
Yes.

1681
01:25:48,784 --> 01:25:49,784
For Table 13.

1682
01:25:49,785 --> 01:25:51,313
(Pan of the squid and pork: 4 out 5)

1683
01:25:51,314 --> 01:25:52,483
This is for Table Six.

1684
01:25:52,484 --> 01:25:54,284
(Pan of the squid and pork: 5 out 5)

1685
01:25:55,354 --> 01:25:57,323
You can get ready for Table 17 now.

1686
01:25:57,324 --> 01:25:59,224
(Another order came in.)

1687
01:25:59,694 --> 01:26:01,993
(Giving more work)

1688
01:26:01,994 --> 01:26:02,994
It's for two.

1689
01:26:03,864 --> 01:26:06,563
(The pan of the master's spicy stir-fried squid and pork is here.)

1690
01:26:06,564 --> 01:26:07,604
Enjoy.

1691
01:26:07,834 --> 01:26:09,804
Let's try the squid first.

1692
01:26:11,434 --> 01:26:13,704
(Picking up a piece of squid right away)

1693
01:26:14,204 --> 01:26:15,773
(The woman grabs the rice...)

1694
01:26:15,774 --> 01:26:18,444
(and drops it into the pan.)

1695
01:26:19,114 --> 01:26:20,444
You're smart.

1696
01:26:20,984 --> 01:26:22,643
I have my ways.

1697
01:26:22,644 --> 01:26:25,054
It's smart of you to add the rice to the sauce.

1698
01:26:27,054 --> 01:26:30,554
(This time, she creates space by pushing it to the side.)

1699
01:26:30,624 --> 01:26:34,464
(Then she pours the rice into it.)

1700
01:26:35,024 --> 01:26:36,184
You're adding the whole bowl.

1701
01:26:36,764 --> 01:26:39,464
(Adding his rice after her)

1702
01:26:39,934 --> 01:26:44,234
(They fried the rice in the sauce for a while.)

1703
01:26:45,234 --> 01:26:47,703
Excuse me. I was curious about the menu.

1704
01:26:47,704 --> 01:26:50,974
(He tries to read the menu.)

1705
01:26:52,074 --> 01:26:55,013
Roughly speaking, there's a pan...

1706
01:26:55,014 --> 01:26:56,553
of pork and squid.

1707
01:26:56,554 --> 01:26:58,783
It comes with a little bit of rice and a small salad.

1708
01:26:58,784 --> 01:27:01,523
Two people can share one.

1709
01:27:01,524 --> 01:27:02,884
(Nailing the explanation)

1710
01:27:03,124 --> 01:27:04,823
(He got his answers.)

1711
01:27:04,824 --> 01:27:08,124
I sounded as if I were working here.

1712
01:27:09,524 --> 01:27:11,084
You're almost like a staff member here.

1713
01:27:11,664 --> 01:27:13,034
Not at all.

1714
01:27:13,634 --> 01:27:15,533
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

1715
01:27:15,534 --> 01:27:17,034
(He leaves after thanking her.)

1716
01:27:18,034 --> 01:27:19,274
Their strategy is working.

1717
01:27:21,104 --> 01:27:23,843
I should use this tactic in my restaurant too.

1718
01:27:23,844 --> 01:27:26,243
Yes. It's a good idea to set up a big window...

1719
01:27:26,244 --> 01:27:28,614
so that you can see from the outside.

1720
01:27:29,314 --> 01:27:31,414
When presented like that,

1721
01:27:31,554 --> 01:27:33,424
it triggers people's curiosity.

1722
01:27:34,454 --> 01:27:38,754
(Optimized to spark curiosity)

1723
01:27:39,924 --> 01:27:41,924
They do what they need to do to lure customers in.

1724
01:27:43,434 --> 01:27:45,594
They have a good business philosophy.

1725
01:27:46,404 --> 01:27:49,164
Asian food is popular in Europe.

1726
01:27:49,674 --> 01:27:51,804
Especially grilling food...

1727
01:27:52,734 --> 01:27:55,074
on a pan like this.

1728
01:27:55,344 --> 01:27:58,844
(Overall review: Great concept)

1729
01:27:59,574 --> 01:28:02,544
(The industry peers' sharp analysis continues.)

1730
01:28:03,414 --> 01:28:05,554
Now, we...

1731
01:28:09,794 --> 01:28:11,854
- We have many people waiting.
- Okay.

1732
01:28:14,764 --> 01:28:16,764
We have 16 people waiting.

1733
01:28:17,794 --> 01:28:19,593
Should we stop taking customers?

1734
01:28:19,594 --> 01:28:21,763
- Why?
- There are 16 more people.

1735
01:28:21,764 --> 01:28:23,103
- Why?
- Do we keep taking more?

1736
01:28:23,104 --> 01:28:24,104
Of course.

1737
01:28:25,134 --> 01:28:26,804
We need to get it done today.

1738
01:28:29,304 --> 01:28:31,743
(Chef Paik wants to see it through the end...)

1739
01:28:31,744 --> 01:28:34,214
(while the employees are exhausted.)

1740
01:28:34,684 --> 01:28:36,384
Gosh. My legs.

1741
01:28:37,854 --> 01:28:39,084
Cheer up, Si Jin.

1742
01:28:40,654 --> 01:28:42,824
- Let's go for 2,000 euros.
- Yes.

1743
01:28:43,224 --> 01:28:44,594
No. The sales are important.

1744
01:28:45,024 --> 01:28:46,153
I think we can get it.

1745
01:28:46,154 --> 01:28:49,664
(Will they reach the goal early with today's business?)

1746
01:28:50,035 --> 01:28:52,575
(We'll reveal the result of making 1 million dollars a year.)

1747
01:28:52,775 --> 01:28:55,545
(After the intense 7-day business, )

1748
01:28:55,915 --> 01:28:57,244
(they're about to accomplish...)

1749
01:28:57,245 --> 01:28:58,885
(the mission to reach 1 million dollars.)

1750
01:28:59,015 --> 01:29:02,085
(They're appalled...)

1751
01:29:02,615 --> 01:29:04,585
(by the shocking result.)

1752
01:29:04,825 --> 01:29:07,794
No. Didn't you do the calculations wrong?

1753
01:29:07,795 --> 01:29:08,855
John.

1754
01:29:09,725 --> 01:29:10,825
Goodness.

1755
01:29:11,265 --> 01:29:12,265
Hey!

1756
01:29:12,495 --> 01:29:13,695
I can't believe this.

1757
01:29:14,565 --> 01:29:16,035
(And...)

1758
01:29:16,595 --> 01:29:17,935
After a week.

1759
01:29:18,305 --> 01:29:22,035
(The story that has been untold)

1760
01:29:23,205 --> 01:29:29,245
(Their last story)

1761
01:29:51,600 --> 01:29:53,600
Dramaday.me
